<title>NieR:Automata Stage Plays</title>
<p class="title">Stage Play Information:</p>
<p class="para">YoRHa Ver1.0 was the first stage play, lasting from October 1st, 2014 to October 5th, 2014. It ties into NieR:Automata's story, yet predates the release.</p>
<p class="para">YoRha Ver1.1 was the second stage play lasting from May 23rd, 2015 to May 31st, 2015. It never released commerically.</p>
<p class="para">YoRHa Ver1.2 Was the third stage play, lasting from February 9th, 2018 to February 13t, 2018. Notably, after NieR:Automata's release. Notably, it had a higher budget.<br>They Removed the characters Sonia, Erica, Shion, Kalmia, Clematis, and Seed. They also added the character Daisy.</p>
<p class="para">YoRHa Ver1.3a/aa had some significant changes to the story, notably making the cast all male. Ver1.3a isn't currently available, but you can watch Ver1.3aa here. Between the two versions, 1.3aa removed Anemone and added Jackass.</p>
<p class="line"></p>
<p class="para">YoRha Boys Ver1.0 is a different story, telling the tale of an all male YoRHa squadron. It ran from January 31st, 2018 to February 4th, 2018.</p>
<p class="para">YoRHa Girls Ver1.1a is a genderbent version of YoRHa Boys, and a different setting. It ran from December 3rd, 2020 to December 6th, 2020.</p>
